Results: 56 out of 119 candidates were allocated in the intervention group. No signiﬁcant differences between age, sex were observed between groups. QCPR global score was 70.5\% (SD: 23.0\%) in the control group vs 68.4\% (SD: 21.4\%) in the intervention group (p = 0.618). Mean chest compression depth was 50.34 vs 50.21 (p = 0.935), mean compressions rate 105.52 vs 107.90 (p = 0.401). Mean breathing volume 759 ml vs 642 ml (p =v0.054)
Conclusions: No difference was found in high quality CPR between both teaching methods. New studies with more sample size would be recommended to conﬁrm these results.},
